<description>
 <p>
   <b>SC4 part number:</b>  </p>
 <p>
   <b>(2) Clause:</b> 10303-1016
 </p>
 <p>
   <b>(3) Paragraph:</b> 
 </p>
 <p>
   <b>(5) Comment:</b>
 </p>
 <p>
There is a big overlap between product_category and class. From the evolution of STEP it must be clear that product_category shall only be used for AP-specify categories, but not for typical application data. In the latter case Class (10303-1070) even for products has to be used
</p>
 <p>
   <b>(6) Proposal:</b>
 </p>
 <p>
Change introduction to "This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the representation of structured hierarchies of AP or module specific categories for products."
4.1.1 Change to "A Product_category is a type of product for AP or module specific purpose."
Add a note: "For the purpose of a general classification of products use entity Class and Classification_assignment ISO 10303-1070 and -1114". (where
In 4.1.1 change the example to "part" and "document".
An alternative would to remove this module completely - it is not really needed!</p>
 </description>

